Right, well New Zealand will be rather pleased with their effort to restrict Australia to under 300. Most of the Australian batsmen got starts but they seemed to struggle with the pace of the wicket at times and were unable to push on. Some good death bowling from Southee and Bond complemented the earlier efforts of Tuffey and Franklin.

Join us in 30 minutes when New Zealand begin their chase against a very very good Australian pace attack. It will be interesting to see how much of a difference Doug Bollinger makes after not playing the T20Is.

Can McCullum continue his recent run of form or will Bollinger, Harris and Johnson be far too good?
